def: To handle or manage awkwardly; to crowd or tumble together.Shak.

To drink spirituous or strong liquors habitually; to indulge inthe frequent and improper used of spirituous liquors; especially, todrink frequently in small quantities, but without absolutedrunkeness.Few of those who were summoned left their homes, and those fewgenerally found it more agreeable to tipple in alehouses than to pacethe streets. Macaulay.
The act of deluding one's self, or the state of being thusdeluded.
Any mollusk which has a shell composed of more than two pieces.
The lower or lowest side of anything. Paley.
Freedom from passion; an undisturbed state; apathy. Sir W.Temple.
A writer of pamphlets; a scribbler. Dryden. Macaulay.
The pomegranate tree (Punica granatum). The bark of the root,the rind of the fruit, and the flowers are used medicinally.
